            <head>Biographical Note</head>

            <p>Harris and Vonnegut, classmates at Cornell University during the 1940's, worked for
                the <emph render="italic">Cornell Daily Sun</emph> during their years at Cornell. In
                1942-1943, Harris served as the paper's Editor-in-Chief while the younger Vonnegut
                served as his Associate Editor- in-Chief. Founded in 1880, The <emph render="italic"
                    >Cornell Daily Sun</emph> is one of the nation's oldest independent daily
                college newspapers. Harris went on to be associated as an executive with the Eagle
                Shirt Company.</p>

